The paper focuses on using weighted PageRank algorithms to measure the popularity and prestige of scholars from a citation perspective in the field of Information Retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with data collection and analysis, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of Web of Science (WOS) for data collection and analysis suggests a focus on digital libraries, which could fall under cs.DL. The paper also discusses the relationships among different measures, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
